    <p>It was their son’s de­gen­er­a­tive eye dis­ease that set a cou­ple on the path of phi­lan­thropy. In 2011, they set up the char­ity iC2 PrepHouse, which teaches chil­dren with low vi­sion the skills to cope with daily life and sup­ports them to re­main in main­stream schools. They now plan to leave $200,000 or more in their will to char­ity.</p>


